> "Can go top and outdamage Riven" is probably not near as much of a reasonable expectation as "isn't forced into support only." I think I've mentioned this elsewhere, but I'm doing his upcoming gameplay update and have no real issues with him being playable in roles outside of support. That said, he will most likely be balanced to be played in the support position, but I'd like people to be able to have fun and win with him elsewhere if it's not compromising his overall power level.

I would still like him to be a Riven counter tho. 
